@startuml states
title Job lifecycle — the universal state machine
skinparam shadowing false

[*] --> QUEUED : submit

QUEUED --> HELD : no slot can EVER satisfy\nrequirements (admission, #8)
HELD --> QUEUED : constraints / budget / facts change
HELD --> CANCELLED : user cancel

QUEUED --> PLACING : reserve slot (atomic txn)
QUEUED --> CANCELLED : user cancel

PLACING --> RUNNING : provider.place() ok
PLACING --> QUEUED : place failed (attempts++)
PLACING --> CANCELLED : user cancel

RUNNING --> SUCCEEDED : result.json, exit 0
RUNNING --> QUEUED : LOST / ghost / preempted\n(reconcile re-queues — never wedged)
RUNNING --> FAILED : exit != 0 & retries exhausted
RUNNING --> CANCELLED : user cancel\n(SIGTERM -> SIGKILL, then reap)

SUCCEEDED --> [*]
FAILED --> [*]
CANCELLED --> [*]

note right of QUEUED
  A job that is not explicitly cancelled
  always eventually runs (liveness invariant).
end note
@enduml
